# Override npm's default script runner from cmd.exe to PowerShell.
#
# Root cause: npm on Windows uses `cmd.exe /d /s /c "<script>"` to run
# lifecycle scripts. cmd.exe cannot operate in a UNC working directory
# (\\?\c:\...) and silently falls back to C:\Windows, breaking every
# relative path in every npm script.
#
# PowerShell handles UNC paths natively (the developer is already running
# inside a UNC-path PowerShell session). Setting script-shell here applies
# project-wide, fixes the issue permanently, and requires no changes to
# how the developer invokes npm.
#
# Reference: https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/using-npm/config#script-shell
script-shell=powershell.exe
